Hey. Hey.

266
00:18:04,719 --> 00:18:07,677
Carrie, what the hell?
Talk to me.

267
00:18:07,681 --> 00:18:09,718
You heard me.
I changed my mind.

268
00:18:09,719 --> 00:18:11,694
What's going on?

269
00:18:11,698 --> 00:18:13,715
Huh? Tell me.

270
00:18:13,718 --> 00:18:14,711
I can't say.

271
00:18:14,715 --> 00:18:15,732
Can't or won't.
Both.

272
00:18:16,635 --> 00:18:17,702
What am I supposed
to tell Keane?

273
00:18:17,704 --> 00:18:20,637
That my kid is sick.

274
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:21,921
They still won't let me see her.

275
00:18:36,647 --> 00:18:37,642
Hello?

276
00:18:37,647 --> 00:18:38,726
Tell Dar Adal he wins.

277
00:18:38,731 --> 00:18:40,676
Now I want to see my daughter.

278
00:18:41,676 --> 00:18:42,681
Hello?

279
00:18:50,638 --> 00:18:51,710
What do you mean she flaked?

280
00:18:51,715 --> 00:18:53,660
Showed up for the deposition,

281
00:18:53,666 --> 00:18:56,641
then suddenly changed her mind
about the whole thing.

282
00:18:56,644 --> 00:18:57,722
No explanation?

283
00:18:57,724 --> 00:19:00,724
None... just walked out
right after she was sworn in.

284
00:19:00,728 --> 00:19:02,716
Can't say
I'm entirely surprised.

285
00:19:02,720 --> 00:19:05,673
She was wobbly on the idea
from the get-go.

286
00:19:05,675 --> 00:19:08,663
Well, then, this won't come
as a galloping shock, either.

287
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:09,679
What won't?

288
00:19:09,682 --> 00:19:13,646
I've got Dar Adal
waiting outside... unscheduled.

289
00:19:14,663 --> 00:19:15,704
Coincidence?

290
00:19:15,708 --> 00:19:17,674
What do you think?

291
00:19:17,676 --> 00:19:19,691
So he found out
about the deposition somehow

292
00:19:19,693 --> 00:19:23,658
and got to Carrie before
she could go on the record.

293
00:19:23,662 --> 00:19:26,669
It is what he does.

294
00:19:26,672 --> 00:19:27,952
Where does
this leave us, George?

295
00:19:28,636 --> 00:19:30,642
I was just thinking about that.

296
00:19:30,644 --> 00:19:31,702
We're down to Saul Berenson,

297
00:19:31,706 --> 00:19:34,636
that is if you're willing
to offer him a deal

298
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:36,636
in exchange for his testimony.

299
00:19:36,640 --> 00:19:38,698
More than willing.
Is there a legal basis for it?

300
00:19:38,703 --> 00:19:40,712
As long as you go
through proper channels

301
00:19:40,715 --> 00:19:44,637
at justice,
the national security division.

302
00:19:44,641 --> 00:19:45,721
In that case,
FBI counterintelligence

303
00:19:45,724 --> 00:19:47,727
would make
the first approach to Saul.

304
00:19:47,729 --> 00:19:49,666
Think he'll go for it?

305
00:19:49,671 --> 00:19:54,645
If he believes the alternative
is arrest and prosecution.

306
00:19:54,647 --> 00:19:56,700
Start the process.
You'll coordinate, rob?

307
00:19:56,705 --> 00:19:57,697
Yes, ma'am.

308
00:19:57,700 --> 00:19:59,659
Thanks, gentlemen.

309
00:20:04,639 --> 00:20:05,709
Send in Mr. Adal.

310
00:20:16,647 --> 00:20:19,666
Madame president-elect.
Thank you, agent Thoms.

311
00:20:19,669 --> 00:20:21,649
What happened to your face?

312
00:20:21,653 --> 00:20:22,683
Oh.

313
00:20:22,686 --> 00:20:24,703
It's a... it's a fight.

314
00:20:24,708 --> 00:20:27,683
Believe it or not,
with an old friend.

315
00:20:27,687 --> 00:20:29,642
He thought I was responsible

316
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:31,648
for something
I had nothing to do with.

317
00:20:31,650 --> 00:20:32,662
Really?

318
00:20:32,665 --> 00:20:33,729
It happens.

319
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:35,721
So what do you want?

320
00:20:35,726 --> 00:20:39,646
I wasn't satisfied with the way
our meeting went yesterday.

321
00:20:39,649 --> 00:20:41,666
I felt you weren't, either,
and so,

322
00:20:41,668 --> 00:20:44,666
those names you requested
for cabinet positions...

323
00:20:44,668 --> 00:20:45,677
I have them now.

324
00:20:47,730 --> 00:20:50,634
Because this...

325
00:20:50,635 --> 00:20:52,672
Friction between us...

326
00:20:52,677 --> 00:20:54,681
It has to end.

327
00:21:02,732 --> 00:21:06,710
And you think
this would help end

328
00:21:06,714 --> 00:21:09,656
the... Friction?

329
00:21:09,659 --> 00:21:10,669
I know it would.

330
00:21:10,671 --> 00:21:12,666
Three candidates
I would never consider

331
00:21:12,669 --> 00:21:15,705
for any position at any time.

332
00:21:15,708 --> 00:21:17,663
I'm sorry you feel that way.

333
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:20,675
You can't really have expected
anything different.

334
00:21:22,672 --> 00:21:24,697
Actually, I did.

335
00:21:24,701 --> 00:21:26,672
And I'd ask you to reconsider...

336
00:21:26,676 --> 00:21:27,724
advise you to.

337
00:21:27,728 --> 00:21:30,654
So this is your idea of advice?

338
00:21:30,658 --> 00:21:33,666
Does it really matter
what we call it?

339
00:21:33,670 --> 00:21:36,662
Not if we're both clear
on what's really going on.

340
00:21:37,722 --> 00:21:39,685
You think
you know better than me.

341
00:21:39,689 --> 00:21:41,715
When it comes
to the defense of this country,

342
00:21:41,719 --> 00:21:43,661
I'm certain I do.

343
00:21:43,666 --> 00:21:44,689
Oh, you're certain?

344
00:21:44,691 --> 00:21:47,658
I've been at this
a very long time.

345
00:21:47,661 --> 00:21:48,653
At what?

346
00:21:49,678 --> 00:21:53,637
What is it you think
you have been at, exactly?

347
00:21:56,672 --> 00:21:58,694
No, I really want to know.

348
00:22:00,663 --> 00:22:03,643
Keeping America safe.

349
00:22:03,646 --> 00:22:04,701
I see.

350
00:22:04,705 --> 00:22:08,643
And this qualifies
in your opinion?

351
00:22:08,647 --> 00:22:11,652
What does?
Feeding me bad intelligence,

352
00:22:11,655 --> 00:22:13,702
leaking false reports
to the press,

353
00:22:13,706 --> 00:22:15,694
coercing me into cabinet choices

354
00:22:15,697 --> 00:22:17,676
antithetical to the policy goals

355
00:22:17,678 --> 00:22:19,636
that got me elected.

356
00:22:19,639 --> 00:22:22,711
Seriously, where do you see
this going?

357
00:22:22,715 --> 00:22:25,656
Do I come around
to your point of view?

358
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:28,690
Do I give up, roll over?
Do you see me resigning?

359
00:22:31,712 --> 00:22:35,637
I am the next president
of the United States.

360
00:22:35,641 --> 00:22:37,683
Sixty million people
voted for me.

361
00:22:37,688 --> 00:22:40,730
Who the hell voted for you?

362
00:22:40,733 --> 00:22:42,678
Nobody.

363
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:44,647
That's right.

364
00:22:44,650 --> 00:22:46,725
But I have a constituency, too.

365
00:22:48,676 --> 00:22:50,667
What's that supposed to mean?

366
00:22:50,673 --> 00:22:52,729
It means don't go to war

367
00:22:52,731 --> 00:22:57,643
with your own national
security establishment.

368
00:23:00,637 --> 00:23:02,652
Are you threatening me now?

369
00:23:02,655 --> 00:23:06,677
I'm telling you
it's a war you won't win.

370
00:23:14,648 --> 00:23:16,670
Two hundred and fifty years
of movement

371
00:23:16,675 --> 00:23:18,687
toward the light
in this country,

372
00:23:18,692 --> 00:23:22,684
towards justice...

373
00:23:22,687 --> 00:23:24,684
Say what you want,
call me naive,

374
00:23:24,688 --> 00:23:27,663
but I believe in that light.

375
00:23:27,666 --> 00:23:30,680
And I will not be held hostage
by you or anybody else.

376
00:23:32,717 --> 00:23:36,677
I'm afraid you're taking
this personally, madam.

377
00:23:36,680 --> 00:23:38,702
You're god damn right I am.

378
00:23:48,648 --> 00:23:51,712
I'm sorry if I upset you.

379
00:23:51,715 --> 00:23:53,720
In the future,
in case you're wondering,

380
00:23:53,724 --> 00:23:57,716
this moment, right now,

381
00:23:57,719 --> 00:24:00,696
is when I decided
to put your ass in jail.

382
00:24:05,717 --> 00:24:07,683
Good day.

383
00:24:18,665 --> 00:24:19,658
Hello?

384
00:24:19,661 --> 00:24:20,718
It's me.
Well?

385
00:24:20,722 --> 00:24:23,638
Apparently,
my powers of persuasion

386
00:24:23,642 --> 00:24:24,708
aren't what they used to be.

387
00:24:24,712 --> 00:24:27,669
Time to weaponize
some information.

388
00:24:27,672 --> 00:24:29,716
Afraid so.

389
00:24:56,722 --> 00:24:59,639
Told you... nobody home.

390
00:24:59,642 --> 00:25:00,705
Guess not.

391
00:25:00,709 --> 00:25:02,652
I did what you said.

392
00:25:05,723 --> 00:25:07,656
Hey.

393
00:25:07,659 --> 00:25:10,706
Next time,
you ask for half up front.

394
00:26:03,725 --> 00:26:05,667
No, you don't!

395
00:26:09,676 --> 00:26:12,693
You f...
you fucking assholes.

396
00:26:14,718 --> 00:26:17,650
About fucking time.

397
00:26:17,652 --> 00:26:18,688
Assholes... all of you.

398
00:26:21,710 --> 00:26:23,727
Grab yourself a beer
and let's get started.

399
00:26:23,731 --> 00:26:27,634
Those of you with families
won't be going home tonight.

400
00:26:27,636 --> 00:26:29,703
Those of you with hot dates,
consider them iced.

401
00:26:29,706 --> 00:26:31,678
Bus is coming for us in 90.

402
00:26:31,681 --> 00:26:33,698
Sorry for the late notice,
gentlemen,

403
00:26:33,701 --> 00:26:35,712
but Intel just found us
some shitheads.

404
00:26:35,715 --> 00:26:38,703
Who?
Al-Shabaab this time.

405
00:26:38,707 --> 00:26:41,712
Fuckers killed eight of ours.
Well, now they're fucked.

406
00:26:43,713 --> 00:26:44,721
Yo, Quinn, catch.

407
00:27:10,707 --> 00:27:11,715
Shut that thing off.

408
00:27:12,724 --> 00:27:15,694
This sucks.
I cooked last night.

409
00:27:15,699 --> 00:27:17,716
Yeah, and it was shit.
Says who?

410
00:27:17,719 --> 00:27:19,706
Says me.

411
00:27:19,708 --> 00:27:22,636
The deal is do it
till you do it right.

412
00:27:51,659 --> 00:27:52,659
Hello?

413
00:27:52,661 --> 00:27:54,681
Carrie, hi.
It's Christine Lonas.

414
00:27:54,686 --> 00:27:56,636
Did you hear from the doctor?

415
00:27:56,640 --> 00:27:58,715
I did, and let me just
apologize right off the bat

416
00:27:58,720 --> 00:28:01,710
for worrying you unnecessarily.

417
00:28:01,712 --> 00:28:04,645
What do you mean?
Well, it turns out it wasn't

418
00:28:04,649 --> 00:28:05,695
Franny who was sick after all.

419
00:28:05,699 --> 00:28:09,674
It was another girl at the home.
I see.

420
00:28:09,678 --> 00:28:12,654
My supervisor took the call
early this morning.

421
00:28:12,658 --> 00:28:15,691
It was an honest mistake.

422
00:28:16,692 --> 00:28:17,722
I see.

423
00:28:17,725 --> 00:28:20,662
Anyway, the good news is
we can keep our appointment

424
00:28:20,664 --> 00:28:23,642
as scheduled if that's
still good for you.

425
00:28:29,668 --> 00:28:30,713
Carrie?

426
00:28:30,715 --> 00:28:32,668
Um, yes, yes.
I'll be there.

427
00:28:32,673 --> 00:28:33,715
A-and thank you.

428
00:28:43,683 --> 00:28:44,694
May we?

429
00:29:18,706 --> 00:29:20,676
Could we have
some privacy, please?

430
00:29:27,635 --> 00:29:29,666
I'm sure you can guess
why I'm here.

431
00:29:32,646 --> 00:29:33,683
My deposition...

432
00:29:33,686 --> 00:29:35,733
you want to know
why I didn't go through with it.

433
00:29:36,636 --> 00:29:38,673
Yes, though, honestly,
I might have some idea.

434
00:29:41,670 --> 00:29:43,687
My priorities shifted.

435
00:29:43,689 --> 00:29:45,707
Really?

436
00:29:45,711 --> 00:29:48,654
Well, let me tell you
what happened to me today

437
00:29:48,656 --> 00:29:50,816
just about the same time
your priorities were shifting.

438
00:29:51,636 --> 00:29:53,646
Dar Adal paid me
a surprise visit

439
00:29:53,650 --> 00:29:55,676
with three candidates
for my cabinet...

440
00:29:55,682 --> 00:29:59,660
Mercer, Westlake, and Stewart.

441
00:29:59,665 --> 00:30:01,672
Glenallen Stewart
actually signed a letter

442
00:30:01,674 --> 00:30:03,677
during the campaign
saying I was unfit

443
00:30:03,682 --> 00:30:06,691
to be commander in chief.

444
00:30:06,694 --> 00:30:08,708
So I have to ask...

445
00:30:08,711 --> 00:30:10,700
what would embolden Dar Adal

446
00:30:10,703 --> 00:30:13,668
to make such
an extreme recommendation,

447
00:30:13,672 --> 00:30:14,717
and why now?

448
00:30:18,651 --> 00:30:19,659
I have no idea.

449
00:30:19,662 --> 00:30:22,671
Come on, Carrie.
You know exactly why.

450
00:30:24,635 --> 00:30:26,681
He found out
you were advising me,

451
00:30:26,685 --> 00:30:27,693
and he got to you,

452
00:30:27,697 --> 00:30:30,707
just like he got
to Majid Jivadi before.

453
00:30:30,710 --> 00:30:33,660
Tell me what he's holding
over your head.

454
00:30:39,723 --> 00:30:41,639
Is it your daughter?

455
00:30:44,717 --> 00:30:47,640
You asked me
about that situation.

456
00:30:47,643 --> 00:30:49,657
And you said
you couldn't get involved.

457
00:30:49,660 --> 00:30:51,665
So it is your daughter.

458
00:30:51,671 --> 00:30:52,712
No.
Don't lie to me.

459
00:30:52,716 --> 00:30:56,724
Then don't ask me questions
you know I can't answer.

460
00:30:56,728 --> 00:30:59,688
And don't show up here
with a platoon of armed men

461
00:30:59,691 --> 00:31:02,675
and tell yourself you're not
trying to strong-arm me, too.

462
00:31:07,634 --> 00:31:08,722
Now, I was just leaving.
So that's it.

463
00:31:08,726 --> 00:31:11,701
This is all fine with you.
He gets a free pass...

464
00:31:11,706 --> 00:31:13,718
My daughter is waiting.
...A man you said

465
00:31:13,723 --> 00:31:16,676
was responsible for the
brutal murder of your client

466
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:18,668
and the execution
of an FBI agent.

467
00:31:18,673 --> 00:31:20,640
I have to go.
Carrie!

468
00:31:22,677 --> 00:31:23,719
I can't.

469
00:31:51,652 --> 00:31:52,696
Mrs. Berenson?

470
00:31:53,702 --> 00:31:54,700
That's right.

471
00:31:54,702 --> 00:31:56,694
A man left this message for you.

472
00:31:56,697 --> 00:31:57,730
He said he's very sorry.

473
00:31:59,702 --> 00:32:01,647
Thank you.

474
00:32:08,690 --> 00:32:10,648
"My apologies, Mira."

475
00:32:10,652 --> 00:32:12,652
It's an emergency,

476
00:32:12,654 --> 00:32:15,685
and I need to be absolutely
certain of a private meeting.

477
00:32:15,687 --> 00:32:18,636
If you can find it
in your heart,

478
00:32:18,638 --> 00:32:20,658
please follow
the directions below.

479
00:32:20,663 --> 00:32:22,699
You were always curious
about my work.

480
00:32:22,703 --> 00:32:26,703
Well, this is called
paper-chasing.

481
00:32:26,705 --> 00:32:29,658
Please pay the bill
and leave the cafe immediately,

482
00:32:29,664 --> 00:32:31,692
turning right
and onto 77th street.

483
00:32:31,697 --> 00:32:33,692
"Midway down the block,
cross the street."

484
00:32:35,731 --> 00:32:38,676
"At the corner
of central park west,

485
00:32:38,681 --> 00:32:41,673
a silver range rover
will pull up beside you."

486
00:32:42,727 --> 00:32:44,668
"Get in."

487
00:33:10,654 --> 00:33:11,696
Inside... quickly.

488
00:33:17,647 --> 00:33:19,697
Take the elevator...
number 16a.

489
00:33:44,711 --> 00:33:46,675
What the hell, Saul?

490
00:33:46,678 --> 00:33:48,720
Is the world coming
to an end or something?

491
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:54,647
What's going on?

492
00:33:54,650 --> 00:33:57,699
I have to leave...
suddenly.

493
00:33:57,703 --> 00:33:59,681
You won't be seeing me
for a while.

494
00:33:59,684 --> 00:34:01,664
Well, I wasn't exactly
expecting to.

495
00:34:01,668 --> 00:34:02,714
It's been almost two years.

496
00:34:02,718 --> 00:34:04,696
I meant for good.

497
00:34:04,698 --> 00:34:06,651
I'm in trouble.

498
00:34:06,657 --> 00:34:07,677
I have to disappear.

499
00:34:11,677 --> 00:34:13,644
What kind of trouble?

500
00:34:14,714 --> 00:34:16,708
It doesn't matter.

501
00:34:16,711 --> 00:34:18,731
What matters is
they'll come looking for me.

502
00:34:18,733 --> 00:34:20,648
They'll come knocking

503
00:34:20,650 --> 00:34:22,665
on your door first.
- Who's "they," if you

504
00:34:22,667 --> 00:34:24,687
don't mind me asking?
- Counterintelligence.

505
00:34:24,692 --> 00:34:26,670
They'll find you.
They always do.

506
00:34:26,675 --> 00:34:28,679
Not if you don't tell them
where I am.

507
00:34:31,713 --> 00:34:35,679
If I can get to Athens...
and I think I can...

508
00:34:35,683 --> 00:34:39,643
only you and father Matsoukis
know about the rectory.

509
00:34:39,647 --> 00:34:42,638
The rectory?
Of course.

510
00:34:42,644 --> 00:34:45,727
No, no, no. And here
I thought all these years

511
00:34:45,731 --> 00:34:48,636
that it would be
our little hideaway

512
00:34:48,639 --> 00:34:50,701
in the Greek islands.
Let's not do that, Mira.

513
00:34:50,704 --> 00:34:51,728
Please.

514
00:35:01,657 --> 00:35:03,729
So should I just keep
my mouth shut? Is that it?

515
00:35:03,732 --> 00:35:06,686
Most likely, they'll send
someone you know...

516
00:35:06,688 --> 00:35:08,663
Harry Tenzer, Leo Traunfeld.

517
00:35:08,666 --> 00:35:09,730
They'll play nice at first.

518
00:35:09,733 --> 00:35:12,646
And they'll have a story.
What do you mean?

519
00:35:12,650 --> 00:35:14,692
I've gone off on vacation
somewhere, off the grid.

520
00:35:14,697 --> 00:35:16,730
They need to reach me
immediately.

521
00:35:17,634 --> 00:35:19,672
Do I have a favorite place
I like to go,

522
00:35:19,676 --> 00:35:22,701
somewhere I've
always dreamed of going?

523
00:35:22,704 --> 00:35:26,638
And then, it will get uglier.

524
00:35:26,641 --> 00:35:28,668
"Uglier"?
The less you tell them.

525
00:35:30,690 --> 00:35:32,722
They'll call me a traitor,

526
00:35:32,724 --> 00:35:37,672
want to know if I ever talked
of going over to the other side,

527
00:35:37,674 --> 00:35:39,694
selling secrets
to the highest bidder.

528
